    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>Or we choose eco-socialism and choose to struggle towards another world where our relationship with the environment is based on sustainable coexistence, where Indigenous peoples have full control over their land and their destinies, where Black and Indigenous People of Color (BIPOC) everywhere can live in clean air, fresh water, peace, and prosperity.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>Annie Yang is a Trinity senior. Her column, “planting seeds,” runs on alternate Mondays.</em></p>

